Thus, Tor Arntsen wrote...
> What's wrong with 
> #!/bin/env perl
> Now you only have to fix the incorrect path to 'env' on Linux, it should
> be in /bin not /usr/bin, because /bin is where you will find it on 
> IRIX, AIX, Solaris and everywhere I looked.
On FreeBSD, Solaris and Linux I happen to find /usr/bin/env, with there
being no /bin/env on FreeBSD. I don't care where it's *supposed* to be, but
if it's there in /usr/bin everywhere, then I'm sticking to that.
